query.result:
19 The rain makes them howl like dogs;  
20 of one of the sides they make to the other screen;  
21 the miserable profanes often turn themselves.

22 When Cerberus, the great worm, saw us,  
23 the mouths opened and monstrous the sanne;  
24 he had no limb that held firm.

58 I answered them: “Ciacco, your anguish  
59 weighs on me so, that it urges me to weep;  
60 but tell me, if you know, to what they will come  

61 the citizens of the departed city;  
62 if any there is just; and tell me the cause  
63 for which it has such discord assailed”.

73 The just are two, and there are not understood there;  
74 pride, envy and greed are  
75 the three sparks that have the hearts lit.

85 And those: “They are among the darkest souls;  
86 various sins weigh them down at the bottom;  
87 if you descend so far, there you will be able to see them.”

91 He turned his right eye then toward the blind;  
92 He looked at me a little and then bowed his head:  
93 He fell with it equal to the other blind.

